</div> 
<p><strong>Halberd</strong>&nbsp;is a&nbsp;basic <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Halberds" href="/Halberds" target="">Halberd</a> weapon&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Halberd</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>&nbsp;and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>&nbsp;and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for a starting melee weapon choice.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>A long-handled polearm that combines the functions of both axe and spear.&nbsp;</em></p> 
 <p><em>Can be used to press a single enemy with continuous thrusting attacks or swept at groups, taking advantage of its great reach and cleaving blade. A versatile weapon for any situation.&nbsp;</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Halberd in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Halberd weapon can be found at the following locations:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Starting equipment for the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Vagabond" href="/Vagabond" target="">Vagabond</a> class.</li> 
 <li>Can be purchased from the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Nomadic Merchant North Limgrave" href="/Nomadic+Merchant+North+Limgrave">Nomadic Merchant</a>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Limgrave" href="/Limgrave">North Limgrave</a>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;1,200&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Runes" href="/Runes">Runes</a>. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=959&amp;lat=-176.367187&amp;lng=111.488702&amp;zoom=8" href="/Interactive+Map?id=959&amp;lat=-176.367187&amp;lng=111.488702&amp;zoom=8">Elden Ring Map here</a>].</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Halberd Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Charge Forth" href="/Charge+Forth" target="">Charge Forth</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon can be infused with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a>.</li> 
 <li><strong>Halberd</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stones" href="/Smithing+Stones" target="">Smithing Stones</a>.</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>The <strong>Halberd</strong> weapon can be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a>. Click below for a list of all possible Ashes of War that can be applied to the halberd.</p> 
